Class AmpDifferentialColumn<K extends Cell>

    public abstract class AmpDifferentialColumn<K extends Cell>
extends AmpSqlSourcedColumn<K>
    an AMP column which keeps a keyed cache of a column indexed by activity_id in a DifferentialCache, subject to invalidation on db changes or a timeout.
    Implementation-level. it is a two-level cache of cells subject to invalidation. The first level is a cache-of-differential-caches keyed in a construction-specified way. This first level is configured by cacheKeyBuilder.
    The second level is a DifferentialCache which caches on an activity-id-level and fetches/invalidates/refills on a per-column-per-key based accounting. For a visual representation of the way this 2-level cache works and invalidates, please visit documentation here.
    The differential behaviour can be disabled by setting AmpReportsSchema.ENABLE_CACHING to false. This would effectively transform this class into AmpSqlSourcedColumn, thus should only happen during schema debugging
